{"search_data": "ChhattisgarhChhattisgarh Nyuntam Aay Yojana (NYAY) Pilot Project [Income Guarantee Scheme]Chhattisgarh Nyuntam Aay Yojana (NYAY) pilot project to start, 1st state to implement minimum income guarantee scheme, Rs. 72000 p.a to 20% poor people \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u0902Chhattisgarh NYAY Scheme Pilot ProjectThis Nyuntam Aay Yojana in Chhattisgarh is going to boost the rural economy. This NYAY scheme would be a surgical strike on poverty, diesel for the engine of Indian economy and would re-monetize the economy. Now the CG state govt. will deposit an amount of Rs. 6,000 per month directly into the bank accounts of poor people. This would be done through Direct Benefit Transfer (DBT) mode.This move of Chhattisgarh govt. is against the PM Modi\u2019s claim of depositing Rs. 15 lakh in bank account of Indians and bringing back the black money deposited abroad. However, the congress party was unable to create a buzz about the NYAY scheme in the recent elections.CG NYAY Scheme pilot project promises to provide Rs. 72000 per annum to 20% of the poorest families. CG govt. claims that it has necessary fund inputs to keep the economy afloat. This pilot project will start in a small area at first just like the recent pilot project to fight malnutrition in Bastar. This Harik Nani Bera campaign to expand to all districts in Chhattisgarh on 2 October 2019.The work on finalising modalities of the NYAY Scheme is still going on and would soon be chartered out. The state govt. is meeting with various economists and convenor of Congress manifesto committee to lay down the criteria for Universal Basic Income Scheme.In the current economic scenario, NYAY has become even more relevant to inject financial fluidity. NYAY scheme will provide basic level of support to rural income and will enable people to focus on basic amenities like health, education etc.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https:/